17:28.490 --> 17:30.860
Yeah. Oh, well, these are for you.

17:31.030 --> 17:32.360
They're from Mr. Leno.

17:32.530 --> 17:34.690
Oh, thanks.

17:35.260 --> 17:38.170
Listen, John.
How long have you been a standup?

17:38.330 --> 17:40.360
About 10 years. Why?

17:40.700 --> 17:42.170
[WILL SIGHS]

17:42.540 --> 17:45.060
I just hate this part of my job.

17:45.370 --> 17:47.430
What part?

17:48.140 --> 17:49.610
Dude, you've been bumped.

17:50.180 --> 17:51.270
Bumped?

17:51.450 --> 17:54.040
Listen. One of Roseanne's
other personalities showed up.

17:54.220 --> 17:56.310
We're gonna have to let her keep talking.

17:56.720 --> 17:57.810
You gotta be kidding.

17:57.990 --> 17:59.980
My family in Milwaukee
is gonna be watching.

18:00.160 --> 18:03.490
- I got a killer opening bit.
- I'm sorry, bro, that's show biz. Let's go.

18:03.660 --> 18:06.960
No, wait a minute, I got this great joke
about how I'm so pro-black...

18:07.130 --> 18:10.460
...I won't even pick the cotton
out of a bottle of aspirin.

18:13.970 --> 18:16.340
I think I did you a favor, bro. Come on.

18:16.510 --> 18:18.440
But my family is gonna...

18:18.610 --> 18:20.670
- Security.
- Wait...

18:22.380 --> 18:24.440
[BAND INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

18:24.610 --> 18:25.770
Welcome back.

18:25.950 --> 18:29.750
<i>My next guest is a young comedian making
his first appearance on The Tonight Show.</i>

18:29.920 --> 18:33.820
Please give a warm welcome
to a very funny young man, Mr. John Ridley.

18:34.290 --> 18:36.550
[CROWD CHEERING]

18:41.960 --> 18:43.930
Hey, how you doing?

18:44.100 --> 18:49.500
Hey. Well, you know, the other day,
I just had this bottle of aspirin, you know.

18:49.670 --> 18:53.840
But I couldn't take it because I'm black.

18:55.510 --> 19:00.540
What I mean is, you know,
the bottle had cotton in it, you know.

19:00.720 --> 19:01.740
Get it?

19:01.920 --> 19:04.550
Cotton. I'm black.

19:07.060 --> 19:12.020
Well, well, actually, you know,
what I mean is... Um...

19:12.260 --> 19:13.630
JAY:
Hey, wait a minute, wait.

19:13.800 --> 19:16.860
This isn't John. What's going on?
Security, have this guy removed.

19:17.030 --> 19:19.930
Wait. Wait a minute. Hey, Jay, listen.
You gotta listen to me.

19:20.100 --> 19:22.070
I'm the guy that you're suing, Will Smith.

19:22.240 --> 19:24.640
The guy that's been putting the stuff
in the paper?

19:24.810 --> 19:27.970
- Yeah, that's me.
- There's been a lot written about me.

19:28.140 --> 19:32.010
A lot of it untrue. And this seems to be
the gentleman respon... Come over here.

19:32.180 --> 19:35.210
Why don't we settle it right now.
Why don't you sit down here.

19:35.380 --> 19:38.440
You got two minutes to explain yourself.

19:38.920 --> 19:41.190
- Hey.
- All right, tell us what's going on.

19:41.360 --> 19:45.190
Jay, listen. I was just trying
to impress my girlfriend, Lisa.

19:45.360 --> 19:47.350
I like her a lot, you know.

19:47.530 --> 19:52.630
So I just wanted to prove to her
that I wasn't, you know, goofy.

19:53.740 --> 19:54.760
You, goofy?

19:54.940 --> 19:57.600
Gee, I can't imagine
how she got that idea.

19:57.770 --> 20:00.170
- What are you talking about?
- Yeah, me neither, man.

20:00.340 --> 20:04.110
You know, but what happened was,
you know, I was putting together this book.

20:04.280 --> 20:07.680
<i>It was called
Celebrities' Houses At Night.</i>

20:07.850 --> 20:11.180
- It's a good concept, right?
- Yeah, great, great. Yeah, terrific idea.

20:11.350 --> 20:14.690
You know, what happened was, you know,
I just wanted to show Lisa...

20:14.860 --> 20:16.690
...that I was special, you know?

20:17.060 --> 20:20.720
Because I just really don't wanna lose her
because I really like her.

20:20.900 --> 20:22.090
And, well, the pictures...

20:22.260 --> 20:25.130
...I gave them to the guy,
he was supposed to put out my book.

20:25.300 --> 20:28.360
<i>And, you know, he winded up putting it
in the National Inquisitor.</i>

20:28.540 --> 20:30.630
Jay, I never meant
for anything bad to happen.

20:30.810 --> 20:32.900
I didn't mean for the pictures
to be for that.

20:33.080 --> 20:37.210
Listen, America, I just want you to know
it was not oil, it was coffee.

20:37.380 --> 20:41.080
- Jay was pouring coffee out. It wasn't oil.
- Right.

20:41.250 --> 20:44.280
Well, thank you, Smith,
for clearing that up. I appreciate that.

20:44.450 --> 20:46.720
Well, you know, my friends call me Will.

20:46.890 --> 20:49.150
Thanks a lot, Smith.
I really appreciate that.

20:49.330 --> 20:50.520
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

20:50.690 --> 20:53.460
Actually, that's kind of romantic,
I think, though.

20:53.630 --> 20:54.720
I think...

20:54.900 --> 20:57.490
I mean, what you...
You are goofy, and you are an idiot.

20:57.670 --> 21:00.230
That's beside the point.
It's kind of a romantic thing.

21:00.400 --> 21:03.300
And maybe we should drop the suit.
What do you think, audience?

21:07.110 --> 21:08.440
- All right, Will.
- Okay.

21:08.610 --> 21:09.840
You're off the hook.

21:10.010 --> 21:12.070
- Thanks a lot, Jay.
- All right, all right.

21:12.250 --> 21:14.080
Hey, who's our next guest?

21:15.050 --> 21:16.480
[WILL SCREAMS]

21:19.820 --> 21:21.260
[APPLAUSE ON TV]

21:21.420 --> 21:25.420
<i>That's it. Join us tomorrow when our guests
will be Kevin Costner, Wilt Chamberlain...</i>

21:25.590 --> 21:28.120
<i>...and we'll see
if we can find the real John Ridley.</i>

21:28.300 --> 21:30.730
<i>See you later, bye-bye.
Thanks for watching.</i>

21:30.900 --> 21:31.890
[TV TURNS OFF]

21:32.070 --> 21:34.800
- Wow, Will, were you nervous?
- No, no, not really.

21:34.970 --> 21:37.910
Listen, I'm just glad
that whole mess is over.

21:38.070 --> 21:40.300
Will,
I'm sorry I started the whole thing...

21:40.480 --> 21:42.810
<i>...but you looked pretty good
on The Tonight Show.</i>

21:42.980 --> 21:45.640
You were really wacky.

21:49.690 --> 21:53.420
I'm saying...
What do you mean by "wacky"?

